The paper proposes a framework for convolutional networks to achieve rotation-invariance in medical image analysis, specifically in histopathology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new type of convolutional layer, which involves encoding the geometric structure of the special Euclidean motion group SE(2), indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper evaluates the proposed framework on three different histopathology image analysis tasks, suggesting that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
